  "notes": "Lombard. Gallo-Italic language of Lombardy, parts of Piedmont, and Swiss Ticino. ~3.5 million speakers. Reference variety: Western Lombard (Milanese). Key features: (1) Front rounded vowels /y, ø/. (2) Phonemic vowel length. (3) Degemination. (4) Extreme final vowel loss. (5) Intervocalic lenition (Sanga 1984).",
